{
  "texts": [
    "Er 34 is developed for image captioning evaluation.",
    "It evaluates not just the presence of relevant words but also how frequently those words are used in similar contexts, providing higher scores for words that are both pertinent and rare.",
    "In our context, it helps to ensure that the terminology used is not only appropriate but also indicative of the distinctive features in the images, which is crucial for medical reporting.",
    "ROUGE 35 focuses on the longest common subsequence between the generated text and reference texts, suitable for evaluating model performance at the sentence or paragraph level.",
    "Ophthalmic reports often require coherent descriptions of complex clinical information, and ROUGE helps to understand how well the model maintains coherence throughout the information presented."
  ]
}